The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 New Delhi, Sept. 8 (PTI): The Supreme Court today said 95 per cent of movie halls and commercial establishments in the country lacked proper fire-safety arrangements.          
	The court made the observation during a hearing on the Uphaar cinema case where 59 people were killed in a fire in 1997. The CBI has sought enhanced punishment for the Ansal brothers, the owners of the hall.                   
	Chandigarh (PTI): Haryana chief minister Bhupinder Singh Hooda on Monday announced a compensation of Rs 2 lakh to the family of a woman killed during an agitation by temporary teachers in Rohtak on Sunday. Hooda said Raj Rani was killed when some hoodlums opened fire during the protest.                  
	Neyveli (PTI): About 10,000 contract workers at the Neyveli Lignite Corporation began an indefinite strike from Monday, demanding Rs 10 lakh as compensation for the family of a worker who died in an accident while on his shift. The company had offered Rs 5.76 lakh citing rules.                   
	 Mumbai (PTI): A court on Monday granted bail to Meraj-ur-Rehman, ex-husband of actor Sanjay Dutts wife Maanyata. Meraj is accused of escaping from police custody last month. He has been given bail on a personal bond of Rs 7,000                  
	 New Delhi (PTI): Five persons, including an assistant sub-inspector of police, were killed and as many injured when a truck rammed into some vehicles on Sunday night. ASI Balkar Singh was inspecting a minor accident on Grand Trunk Road when the truck hit his car, lost control and hit six other vehicles. Three persons died on the spot and two in hospital.                   
	 Mumbai (PTI): Two persons have been arrested at Dadar railway station for allegedly possessing an illegal gun and five live cartridges. Nazim Azim Khan, 26, and Mahesh Kanojia, 24, were caught during a security check at the station.                                                                                                                         
